// Rule: Each component must be placed in its own folder and include the following three files:
// - component.tsx
// - component.service.ts (contains logic)
// - component.interface.ts (contains interfaces or types)
// - component.styles.ts (contains styles)
//
// For example, if the component is called "button", the structure should look like:
//
// /components/button/
// ├── Button.tsx
// ├── Button.service.ts
// └── Button.interface.ts
// └── Button.styles.ts
//
// This ensures that the UI, business logic, and types are clearly separated and well organized.
